Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.77,0:01:13.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,Diciembre
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:20.51,HnF,,0,0,0,,Diciembre
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.87,0:01:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(129,40)}NdT: es un tipo de saludo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.87,0:01:22.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,Panaino!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:24.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Ey, Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.33,0:01:25.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Buenos días.{Good morning.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.11,0:01:27.01,HnF,,0,0,0,,Buenos diaino.{Good mornaino.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.45,0:01:31.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que era eso.{So it was that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.69,0:01:34.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hm, entonces es cierto que la parte más cercana al faro es la más oscura.{Hm, so it is true that the nearest part of the lighthouse is the darkest.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.04,0:01:38.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensé que podría conseguir algo de azúcar durante el descanso.{I thought I would get some sugar during break time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.74,0:01:42.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eso son donuts? ¡Tienen pinta de serlo!{Are they donuts? They’re donuts, right? They have to be donuts!}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.24,0:01:45.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí, sí que son donuts.{Well, they are donuts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.36,0:01:47.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces son donuts, ¡es perfecto!{So they are donuts! That’s magnificent!}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.71,0:01:51.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora, maestro, ofréceme esos donuts inmediatamente.{Now, my master, please present those donuts to me immediately!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:06.31,HnF,,0,0,0,,Maestro,{My master.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:07.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿qué es esto?{What is it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.48,0:02:10.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué son estos? ¿Un producto nuevo de Mister Donut?{What are these? Are they a new product of Mister Donut?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:12.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.23,0:02:15.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,Senjougahara vino hace poco.{Senjougahara visited just now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:18.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ella me trajo estos donuts en señal de agradecimiento.{She brought me these donuts as a sign of support.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.52,0:02:19.59,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué motivo?{For what reason?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.94,0:02:22.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, aunque me lo preguntes...{Well, if you have to ask me that…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.28,0:02:25.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Supongo que es para animarme con los estudios.{Then it’s to encourage me in my studying for the exams.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:27.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es más barato que en la tienda, ¿no?{It’s cheaper to buy them, is it not?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.60,0:02:31.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Senjougahara me ha hecho estos donuts gratis. {Senjougahara made these donuts for me for no charge.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:35.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Entonces no has pagado nada?{Did you not pay any money, my master?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.45,0:02:39.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,No es muy común que una novia pida dinero por unos refrigerios.{I’ve never heard of a girlfriend that asks for money in exchange for refreshments.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:41.59,HnF,,0,0,0,,No puede ser.{Impossible!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.31,0:02:44.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y pensar que la avaricia podría...{To think that miser would…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.73,0:02:47.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Ten cuidado, maestro!{Be careful, my master!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.70,0:02:49.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Puede que haya algún tipo de veneno ahí.{There could be something in these!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:52.87,HnF,,0,0,0,,Espera un momento, ¿qué tipo de persona crees que es una novia?{Now hold on, what do you think a person’s gilfriend is?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.28,0:02:55.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si hay algo en ellos, será amor.{If anything's in them, it's love.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.23,0:02:59.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,El mes pasado experimentaste personalmente que ese amor{You should’ve personally experienced last month that love}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:01.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,puede convertirse en veneno según sea cocinado, ¿cierto?{can turn into poison depending on how it's cooked, have you not?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:12.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué es este agujero?{What is this hole?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:14.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Agujero?{Hole?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.53,0:03:15.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es sospechoso.{This suspicious hole.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.28,0:03:19.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Puede ser que le hayan metido algo al donut mediante ese agujero.{It’s possible that something was injected into this donut via this hole.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.12,0:03:22.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, deja de actuar como un personaje cliché.{…No, stop trying to act like such a clichéd idiot.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:25.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Los donuts suelen llevar agujeros en ellos.{Donuts are supposed to have holes in them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.61,0:03:26.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué?{Why is that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.64,0:03:31.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Los donuts que tienen un agujero son los llamados {\i1}torus{\i0} donuts.{Donuts like those with the holes in them are a variety of donuts called torus donuts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.20,0:03:36.32,HnF,,0,0,0,,Con ese agujero en el medio, el calor puede circular mejor cuando los fríen.{By making a hole in the center like that, the heat can circulate better when they are fried.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:39.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Entonces esta forma se llama{\i1} torus{\i0}?{So you call this shape a torus?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:44.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Para saber si tienen veneno o no, la mejor forma es probarlos.{If you’re going to check whether or not it’s poisoned, the best way would be to taste it for poison.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:47.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Quieres decir que quieres que los pruebe yo?{Are you telling me to be your poison taster?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:50.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Qué maestro tan cruel tengo!{What a cruel master I have!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.67,0:03:52.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡No tengo palabras!{I have no words!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:53.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora te diré,{Im telling you now,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:57.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,no soy alguien a quien le gusten todos los donuts, ¿sabes?{I’m not someone that thinks all donuts are fine, you know?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.30,0:04:00.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si quieres escapar de mi investigación,{If you want to escape from my investigation,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:03.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,deberías ir a la sucursal de Shinobu en la tienda de Mister Donut,{then you should go to the Mister Donut Shinobu branch store immediately}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:07.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,y comprar el Pon De Ring Nama Choco Golden{and buy the Pon De Ring Nama Choco Golden!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.26,0:04:08.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Te lo puedes creer?{Can you believe it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:12.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es bastante impresionante que puedan crear la forma Nama en el Pon De Ring{It’s already a breakthrough to make a Nama form of the Pon De Ring,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:15.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero luego se coloca como chocolate dorado, ¿sabías?{but then they arranged it like a Golden Chocolate, you know?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:18.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,Todavía no los he probado,{I haven’t tasted it yet,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:22.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,solo imaginando el sabor, puedo sentir las sensaciones en mi boca,{but just by imagining the flavor, I can almost feel it expanding in my mouth,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.90,0:04:27.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,y gritaré, sin importarme lo que los demás piensen.{and I’m certain that I’ll shout, without being afraid of what others might think,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:29.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Japanaino!{esto}{qué}{es?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:31.39,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\pos(488,511)}Ese grito parecía más como para alabar a Japón en la guerra.{The shout seemed more like a war cry praising the country of Japan now}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.68,0:04:44.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Es fantástico!{It’s fantastic!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:47.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Llama a esa tsundere ya! \NQuiero alabarla directamente.{Call that tsundere girl immediately! I wish to praise her directly!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.61,0:04:51.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Has llegado hasta aquí casi sin interactuar con Senjougahara,{You’ve come all this way despite hardly ever interacting with Senjougahara,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:54.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿no sería un poco raro hablar con ella \Nsolo para alabar sus donuts?{so it would be a little weird to suddenly meet with her after being moved by the donut}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:04:58.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y ahora qué haces?{What are you doing?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.09,0:05:00.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, ¿qué es lo que haces tú?{I could ask the same thing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:02.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aún no he terminado.{The poison tasting is not over yet!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:03.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Sí que lo has hecho!{No, it’s over, isn’t it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.53,0:05:06.75,HnF,,0,0,0,,Te lo has comido y has dicho que estaba rico, ¿qué más quieres?{You ate it normally and said it was delicious normally, didn’t you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:09.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,Nunca se sabe,{You never know.} puede ser veneno de efecto tardío.{It could be poison with a delayed effect.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.21,0:05:13.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y por eso, la inspección tiene que continuar.{And so, the poison inspection shall continue.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:18.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si pruebo cuatro muestras más, podré llegar a un resultado.{If I do a comparison inspection of four more samples, I should be able to derive the results.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.62,0:05:19.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cuatro muestras?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.80,0:05:27.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Querida Shinobu, como puedes ver, el número exacto de donuts que quedan es cuatro.{Dear Shinobu-tan, from what I can see, the number of remaining donuts happens to be exactly four.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.06,0:05:31.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡El número exacto! Eso sí que es una coincidencia...{The exact number! Now that is an ideal coincidence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.88,0:05:35.43,HnF,,0,0,0,,No lo es, tan solo has hecho que el experimento se adapte a lo que quieres.{No, you just intentionally set up the experiment to suit your needs!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:37.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Suelta ese plato ahora mismo.{Hand over that plate!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:38.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,No lo haré.{I will not.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:44.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como mi maestro que eres, es mi deber protegerte de cualquier riesgo, por muy improbable que sea.{As my master’s attendant, it is my duty to protect my master from any risk, no matter how small!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.72,0:05:47.49,HnF,,0,0,0,,No finjas estar preocupada solo cuando te conviene.{Don’t act like my attendant only when it’s convenient for you!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:51.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es mi última advertencia, Shinobu. Suelta el plato.{This is your last warning, Shinobu. Hand over that plate!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.30,0:05:54.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,No se te da muy bien negociar, maestro.{You sure are poor at negotiations, my master.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:59.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,Repitiendo una y otra vez que suelte el plato,\N que actitud más testaruda.{Never letting down that stubborn attitude, just persistently repeating 'hand it over.’}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:06.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es por eso que te robaron el amuleto que te dio la especialista.{Isn’t it because of that that the talisman that the boss of the specialists entrusted to you was stolen from you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:13.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si hubieses podido negociar como es debido, no estaríamos en esta situación.{If you had been able to negotiate properly then, then we wouldn’t be trapped in this situation right now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:15.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tienes que pensar lo que haces.{You need to reflect on your actions.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.22,0:06:16.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tú{\i0} eres la última persona de la que quiero escuchar eso.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:21.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué tengo que negociar contigo cada vez que te apetece tomar un donut?{Why do I need negotiation skills to keep you in check}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:27.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,Antes que negociar conmigo,\N deberías refinar tu discreción.{Before negotiation skills, my master, you should first hone your sense of secrecy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.13,0:06:28.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Discreción?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.34,0:06:30.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si tan solo hubieses escondido el talismán en un lugar mejor,{If you had simply hid that talisman in a better place,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.40,0:06:36.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,no habrías tenido que negociar en ningún caso.{you wouldn't have needed to do any negotionating to keep us out of this situation.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:37.75,HnF,,0,0,0,,No saber ocultarlo{Hiding it in such an easy-to-find place}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:38.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,ha causado esta tragedia.{marked the beginning of this tragedy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.97,0:06:42.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si hubiese sido yo, lo hubiera escondido mucho mejor.{If it were me, I would definitely have hidden that talisman better.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.84,0:06:45.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y también habría escondido mejor los donuts.{And I would definitely have hidden the donuts better, as well.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:52.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Maestro, comprende que tu ineptitud es la que nos ha traído a esta incómoda situación.{My master, know that your own foolishness is what brought on our unfortunate circumstances!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.24,0:06:56.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ese caso, dime, Shinobu.{Then, tell me this, Shinobu.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.89,0:07:01.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,Dejando el talismán aparte,\N ¿cómo esconderías los donuts?{Putting aside the talisman case, if it were you, how would you have hidden the donuts?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.73,0:07:07.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si me das cinco minutos podría hacer que los donuts desaparezcan completamente.{If I can just have five minutes, I’ll make these donuts splendidly disappear from your very eyes.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:09.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,Jamás podrás encontrarlos.{You’ll never be able to find them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.05,0:07:11.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,Para el carro,{Now hold on,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:15.99,HnF,,0,0,0,,si te diese cinco minutos, \Nsimplemente te comerías los donuts.{if I gave you five minutes, you’ll just eat the rest of the donuts in that time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.99,0:07:20.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Comértelos y decir que han desaparecido es trampa!{If you just eat them and say 'see, they’re gone!’ then that’s totally cheating!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.97,0:07:24.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿De verdad insinúas que caería tan bajo?{Do you really think I’d use such a crafty trick?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.44,0:07:26.37,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo harías. Sin duda.{You definitely would.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.37,0:07:31.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, no sabría decir si todos ellos, \Npero si fuesen uno o dos, no los volverías a ver.{Well, I don’t know about all four of them, but if it was one or two, I can definitely hide them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:32.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué tal si apostamos?{How about a bet?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.55,0:07:37.49,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tendré cinco minutos para esconder los donuts, y tú tendrás cinco para encontrarlos.{I’ll get five minutes to hide the donuts, and you’ll get five minutes to find them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:45.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,Las normas son, que de los cuatro donuts, los que no encuentres, me los comeré yo.{The rule will be that out of the four donuts, the donuts that you were unable to find will be mine to eat.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.94,0:07:52.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,En otras palabras, si eres capaz de encontrarlos todos, entonces podrás comértelos todos.{In other words, if you are able to find all four of them, my master, then you may eat all four of them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.17,0:07:54.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,De acuerdo, acepto la apuesta.{All right, I got it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.97,0:07:59.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo diré una vez más, comértelos no vale como esconderlos, ¿de acuerdo?{I’ll say this once more, but hiding it does not mean eating it, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.46,0:08:01.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,De acuerdo, de acuerdo.{Of course, of course.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:04.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y ocultarlos en mi escote tampoco está permitido, por supuesto.{And hiding it in my cleavage is also not allowed, of course.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:05.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Dónde hay escote en el pecho de esta niña?{Where on that little girl’s chest would there be any cleavage?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:07.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aún hay otro problema.{There’s still another problem.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:12.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y no tiene que ver con las trampas, sino que es un problema más serio.{And it doesn’t have to do with cheating prevention, but a more realistic problem in regards to the game.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.82,0:08:13.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cuál es?{What is it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.81,0:08:16.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,Estás ligada a mi sombra, ¿no?{You’re bound to my shadow, aren’t you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:21.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿En primer lugar, no hace eso difícil esconder algo de mí?{In that case, wouldn’t it be really hard to hide from me and be secretive in the first place?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.85,0:08:24.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, la única solución es cubrirte los ojos.{Well, the only choice is to use a blindfold.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.89,0:08:42.89,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora el epílogo, o mejor dicho, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:44.76,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Usaste los leggins para cubrirte los ojos?{Using leggings as a blindfold?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.57,0:08:46.30,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pervertido.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.62,0:08:49.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,No te adelantes, Hanekawa.{I’ll stop you there, Hanekawa.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.34,0:08:52.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,No fui yo quien quería usar esos leggins como venda.{It’s not that I wanted to use those leggings as a blindfold myself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.21,0:08:57.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cubrirme los ojos con leggins y taparme la boca con ellos fue obra de Shinobu.{Blindfolding me with leggings, and stuffing leggings into my mouth, it was all Shinobu’s doing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.66,0:08:59.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Taparte la boca con ellos?{Stuffing leggings into your mouth…?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:00.40,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,No sé que estoy diciendo...{Slip of the tongue.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:03.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que quería preguntarte.{Then, Hanekawa, I want to ask you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:05.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Dónde crees que Shinobu escondió los donuts?{Where do you think Shinobu hid the donuts?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.13,0:09:11.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pude encontrar tres de ellos, \Npero el último no estaba por ninguna parte.{I was able to find three of the donuts that she hid, but I couldn’t find the last one.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:17.61,HnF,,0,0,0,,Quiero decir, es mi habitación, ¿no?\N Lo habría encontrado tarde o temprano.{I mean, it’s my room, right? There’s a limit to where you can hide stuff in there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.10,0:09:22.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sospecho que Shinobu se lo comería.{In that case, I can only think that Shinobu must have eaten it…}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.50,0:09:27.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque me cuesta creer que fuese de tal forma contra las reglas.{But after saying that much, it’s hard to believe that she would go against the rules like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:31.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que a pesar de lo que dijiste, sí que confías en Shinobu.{So despite everything you've said you still have faith in Shinobu-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.00,0:09:37.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si confías en ella, entonces tendrá que ser el segundo caso más probable.{Well, if Araragi-kun says so, then she must have gone with the second strongest possibility.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.30,0:09:41.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿El segundo caso?{The second strongest?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Entonces sí que me he dejado un lugar?{So there was something I overlooked?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.62,0:09:46.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,Dijiste que los donuts tenían diferentes tamaños, ¿verdad?{You said the donuts had various sizes, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.36,0:09:54.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, entre los cuatro restantes, el más pequeño podría estar escondido dentro del grande.{Then, among the four remaining donuts, the smallest donut would have been hidden in the largest donut.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:09:57.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Un momento... eso no se puede hacer. {Hold on, you can’t do that, can you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.00,0:09:59.91,HnF,,0,0,0,,Se puede, con un donut frito.{You can, with fried donuts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:04.32,HnF,,0,0,0,,A diferencia del exterior, el interior es blando.\N Solo tienes que apretarlo.{Regardless of the outside, the inside is soft enough. You can just press it in.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.62,0:10:07.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo de dentro puede ser blando,\N pero lo de fuera sigue estando duro, ¿sabes?{The inside may be soft, but the outside is hard, you know?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.02,0:10:10.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si hubiese hecho algo así, lo habría notado.{If you did something like that, then I would’ve seen it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:13.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,El donut ya estaba dividido en dos,{The donut was split in two from the beginning,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:17.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,por lo que no habría necesidad de hacerle nada al exterior.{so there would be no need to do anything to the hard part on the outside.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:21.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Además, la crema podría haber actuado como adhesivo al apretar los dos donuts.{Rather, the cream could act as an adhesive after the other donut was pressed in, maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.96,0:10:24.31,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero como sea... no tengo ninguna prueba...{But anyway… I don’t have any evidence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:27.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,La única que tenía te la has comido.{Since you would have eaten the evidence, Araragi-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.76,0:10:33.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Podrías decir que Shinobu ha escondido el donut en {In that sense, you could say that Shinobu-chan hid the donuts in }{\i1}tu{\i0} estómago, Araragi.{stomach, Araragi-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.04,0:10:37.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero, ¿eso no es inútil?{However, isn’t that bad?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.11,0:10:41.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No era el objetivo de Shinobu comerse los donuts?{Wasn’t Shinobu’s objective to eat the donuts?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.28,0:10:45.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,Que lo ocultase en mi estómago\N no sería una buena idea en este caso.{Having me eat them despite that would be putting the cart before the horse.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:47.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,No habría conseguido lo que quería.{She hasn't fulfilled her objective.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.72,0:10:50.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esa es la parte importante, Araragi.{That’s the important part, Araragi-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.08,0:10:53.79,HnF,,0,0,0,,Básicamente,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.82,0:10:57.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,abandonar sus objetivos a cambio de otra cosa.{abandoning her motives and personal gain.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.36,0:11:00.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,No priorizar sus ambiciones.{Not taking into account her own self-centered opinions.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.25,0:11:05.01,HnF,,0,0,0,,De esta forma, es actuar desinteresado, menospreciarse a uno mismo.{To put it another way, being completely selfless, even at the risk of one’s life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:08.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso es lo que quería enseñarte Shinobu.{That’s the point that Shinobu-chan was teaching you about.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:12.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Sobre negociaciones? ¿Discreción?{…About what, negotiations? Secrecy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.05,0:11:17.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sobre el amor.
